775.sl_trans: Torej, ali naj pridem k vam?

776.en_source: Actually, I was just about to go out with some friends.
776.sl_trans: Pravzaprav sem ravno nameraval iti ven s prijatelji.

780.sl_source: Rekla si, da si zasedena, torej...
780.en_source: You said you were busy, so...
780.sl_trans: Rekli ste, da ste zasedeni, zato...

782.en_source: I guess I'll call you tomorrow.
782.sl_trans: Mislim, da te bom poklical jutri.

784.en_source: I've been looking all over for you.

785.sl_source: Noč in dan sem te iskala po cestah.
785.en_source: I've been wandering the streets day and night, trying to find you.
785.sl_trans: Dan in noč sem taval po ulicah, da bi te našel.

786.sl_source: Joe mi je povedal kje si.
786.en_source: Joe told me where you are.
786.sl_trans: Joe mi je povedal, kje ste.

787.sl_source: Kako to, da me več ne pokličeš?
787.en_source: But how come you never call me anymore?
787.sl_trans: Kako to, da me nikoli več ne pokličeš?

789.en_source: So, how are things going with Dana?

794.sl_source: So ji všeč tvoje plošče in podobno?
794.en_source: ls she into your old records and stuff?
794.sl_trans: Ali se ukvarja z vašimi starimi ploščami in drugimi stvarmi?

796.en_source: I mean, she doesn't dislike that stuff.
796.sl_trans: Mislim, da ji te stvari niso všeč.

798.sl_source: Danes greva nakupovati starine za njeno stanovanje.
798.en_source: Actually, we're supposed to go antique shopping... for her apartment this afternoon.
798.sl_trans: Pravzaprav naj bi šli danes popoldne nakupovat starine... za njeno stanovanje.

801.sl_source: Zagotovo te bom čez vikend kaj poklical.
801.en_source: I'll definitely give you a call this week or something.
801.sl_trans: Ta teden te bom zagotovo poklical ali kaj podobnega.

802.en_source: Are you trying to get rid of me?

803.en_source: I should be going in a few minutes, and...
803.sl_trans: Čez nekaj minut bom odšel in...

804.sl_source: Me ne boš niti vprašal kako sem?
804.en_source: Aren't you even going to ask how I'm doing?
804.sl_trans: Ali me sploh ne boš vprašal, kako mi gre?

807.en_source: It's great to finally meet you.

808.en_source: So, how do you two know each other?

809.sl_source: Presenečena sem, da me še ni omenil.
809.en_source: I'm kind of surprised he hasn't mentioned me.
809.sl_trans: Presenečen sem, da me ni omenil.

812.sl_source: Prav ob njem sem stala, ko si ga prvič poklicala.
812.en_source: In fact, I was standing right next to him... the first day you called.
812.sl_trans: Pravzaprav sem stal tik ob njem... prvi dan, ko ste me poklicali.

813.sl_source: Če me ne bi bilo, te ne bi nikoli poklical nazaj.
813.en_source: You know, if it wasn't for me... he would have never called you back.
813.sl_trans: Če ne bi bilo mene, te ne bi nikoli poklical nazaj.

814.sl_source: Zdaj moram stran, toda včasih bi se lahko kaj videla, Seymour.
814.en_source: Well, I've really got to get going... but I'll stop by and see you sometime, Seymour.
814.sl_trans: No, res moram iti... a se bom še kdaj ustavil in te videl, Seymour.

815.en_source: It really was great to meet you.
815.sl_trans: Res je bilo lepo, da sem vas spoznal.

816.en_source: Now remember, the art show is this Saturday... 7:30 p.m., sharp.
816.sl_trans: Ne pozabite, razstava je to soboto... točno ob 19.30.

817.en_source: I'm gonna really miss all of you people.

818.sl_source: Upam, da ste se vsi kaj naučili.
818.en_source: I hope that each of you feels as if you'll be taking away something from this experience.
818.sl_trans: Upam, da bo vsak od vas imel občutek, da bo od te izkušnje nekaj odnesel.

819.sl_source: Enid, bi se lahko za trenutek pogovorila s teboj?
819.en_source: Enid, can I speak to you for a moment?
819.sl_trans: Enid, ali lahko za trenutek govorim s teboj?

821.sl_source: Prijateljica iz akademije za umetnost in slikarstvo mi je povedala, da lahko izberem enega učenca, ki bo prejel eno leto študija.
821.en_source: I got a call from a close friend of mine... at the Academy of Art and Design... and she tells me I'm allowed to place one student... from your graduating class for a full one-year scholarship.
821.sl_trans: Poklicala me je moja tesna prijateljica z Akademije za umetnost in oblikovanje... in mi povedala, da lahko enega študenta iz vašega maturitetnega razreda uvrstim na celoletno štipendijo.

822.en_source: I took the liberty of submitting your name.
822.sl_trans: Dovolil sem si predložiti vaše ime.

823.sl_source: Kot vem, vključuje spanje, hrano in vse ostalo.
823.en_source: As far as I know it includes housing... and meals and everything.
823.sl_trans: Kolikor vem, vključuje nastanitev, prehrano in vse ostalo.

824.sl_trans: To je res zelo ugodna ponudba.

825.en_source: Let me know as soon as you can, Enid.
825.sl_trans: Sporočite mi takoj, ko boste lahko, Enid.

826.sl_source: To bi lahko bila dobra priložnost zate.
826.en_source: This could be a really great thing for you.
826.sl_trans: To je lahko za vas zelo koristno.

829.en_source: Well, I have some good news.

831.en_source: Are you still looking for a job?

832.sl_source: Maxine ti lahko priskrbi službo pri Computer Station.
832.en_source: Maxine thinks she can get you a job at Computer Station.
832.sl_trans: Maxine meni, da ti lahko priskrbi službo na računalniški postaji.

833.sl_source: Običajno, je potrebno imeti veliko priporočil in vsaj dve leti delovnih izkušenj, toda ona pravi, da jih lahko prepriča.
833.en_source: Normally, you have to have a lot of references.... and at least two years of experience... but she thinks she can convince them.
833.sl_trans: Običajno moraš imeti veliko referenc.... in vsaj dve leti izkušenj ... vendar misli, da jih lahko prepriča.

834.sl_source: Reci ji, da naj kar pozabi.

838.sl_source: Obljubim vam, da bom jaz poskrbela.
838.en_source: Just awful! I will take care of it, I promise you.
838.sl_trans: Preprosto grozno! Poskrbel bom za to, obljubim ti.

839.en_source: I will handle it. Thank you.
839.sl_trans: Za to bom poskrbel sam. Hvala.

841.sl_source: Žal mi je, a moram govoriti z njo.
841.en_source: I'm sorry, I need to speak with her for a second.
841.sl_trans: Oprostite, za trenutek se moram pogovoriti z njo.

844.sl_source: Žal mi je, toda takoj moraš odstraniti tisto sliko.
844.en_source: I am sorry... but you are simply going to have to remove that painting.
844.sl_trans: Žal mi je, ampak to sliko boste morali preprosto odstraniti.

845.en_source: Several of the parents have complained about it already.
845.sl_trans: Več staršev se je že pritožilo zaradi tega.

846.en_source: Well, I will do no such thing.

847.sl_source: Potem pa jo bom odstranila kar sama.
847.en_source: Then I'm going to go over there and take it down myself.
847.sl_trans: Potem bom šel tja in ga sam odstranil.

848.sl_source: Mislim, da bi avtorici morali dati priložnost, da se pogovori s starši o njenih namerah pri tej sliki.
848.en_source: I think we should give the artist a chance... to talk with the parents about her intentions with this piece.
848.sl_trans: Mislim, da bi morali dati umetnici priložnost, da se s starši pogovori o svojih namerah glede tega dela.

849.sl_source: Kot rešitev, bi morali podpirati pogovor, ne pa cenzure.
849.en_source: We should be promoting discussion as a solution... instead of censorship.
849.sl_trans: Namesto cenzure bi morali spodbujati razpravo kot rešitev...

851.sl_source: To je prevelika beseda zate, Roberta.
851.en_source: Oh, that is such a big word for you, Roberta.
851.sl_trans: To je zate tako velika beseda, Roberta.

854.en_source: Thank you, everyone, for your patience.

856.en_source: I don't think she's even here.
856.sl_trans: Mislim, da je sploh ni tukaj.

859.sl_source: Nocoj moram na to prekleto razstavo in rada bi, da greš z menoj.
859.en_source: So there's this stupid art show I'm going to tonight... and I want you to be my date.
859.sl_trans: Danes grem na neumno umetniško razstavo in hočem, da si ti moj spremljevalec.

860.en_source: There's something I want to show you.

861.sl_source: Mislim, da ne bi smel iti s teboj.
861.en_source: Yeah, I... I don't think I should.
861.sl_trans: Ja, jaz... Mislim, da ne bi smela.

863.en_source: I'm already a million hours late.

866.en_source: OK, well, forget the art show.

868.en_source: I really wish I could, Enid, but...
868.sl_trans: Res bi si želel, Enid, ampak...

869.sl_source: Dana je pravkar prišla iz slabe zveze in ne bi rad, da bi si kaj mislila, razumeš?
869.en_source: Dana just got out of a really bad relationship... and I don't want her to have the wrong idea, you know?
869.sl_trans: Dana je pravkar končala zelo slabo razmerje... in nočem, da bi imela napačno predstavo, veš?

872.en_source: They were a present from Dana.

875.sl_source: Kaj pa jaz vem o oblačilih?
875.en_source: I mean, what do I know about clothes?

876.sl_source: Lepo je imeti nekoga, ki skrbi za to.
876.en_source: It's nice to have somebody do all the work for me.
876.sl_trans: Lepo je, da nekdo opravi vse delo namesto mene.

877.en_source: I'll just be in my room.

879.sl_source: Ti je rekla, da me ne smeš več videti?
879.en_source: Did she actually tell you that you can't see me anymore? No.
879.sl_trans: Ali ti je res rekla, da me ne smeš več videti? Ne.

881.sl_source: Preprosto ne razume, kako lahko poznam nekoga kot si ti.
881.en_source: She just doesn't understand how I would know someone like you.
881.sl_trans: Preprosto ne razume, kako lahko poznam nekoga, kot si ti.

882.sl_source: Kaj pa to pomeni, "nekoga kot sem jaz"?
882.en_source: What does that mean, "someone like me"?

887.sl_source: Vi ste edina oseba na tem svetu, ki ji lahko zaupam, ker vem, da vas lahko vedno najdem tukaj.

888.en_source: You're, like, the only person in this world I can count on... because, no matter what, I know you'll always be here.
888.sl_trans: Ti si edina oseba na tem svetu, na katero se lahko zanesem... ker vem, da boš ne glede na vse vedno tukaj.

892.en_source: This is such a weird neighborhood.

893.en_source: This is a totally normal, average neighborhood.
893.sl_trans: To je povsem običajna, povprečna soseska.

896.sl_trans: Kaj? Kaj je narobe z njim?

899.sl_source: Kot da ne bi vedela kaj si misliš.
899.en_source: Yeah, I can tell you really love it.
899.sl_trans: Ja, vidim, da ti je res všeč.

900.en_source: What am I supposed to say?

901.sl_source: Komaj čakam, da bom živela v neki depresivni luknji sredi ničesar.
901.en_source: "Gee, I can't wait to live in some depressing shit-hole... "out in the middle of nowhere"?
901.sl_trans: "Joj, komaj čakam, da bom živel v kakšni depresivni luknji... "sredi ničesar"?

902.sl_source: Se zavedaš, da ti prav nič ne odgovarja?
902.en_source: You know, you hate every single place that we look at.
902.sl_trans: Veste, sovražite vsak kraj, ki si ga ogledamo.

903.sl_source: Zakaj mi preprosto ne poveš, da ne želiš več živeti z menoj.
903.en_source: Why don't you just tell me you don't want to live with me?
903.sl_trans: Zakaj mi preprosto ne rečeš, da ne želiš živeti z mano?

904.sl_source: Ker si povsem zmešana in se obnašaš kot psihopatka.
904.en_source: Because you'll totally freak out and act like a psycho about it.
904.sl_trans: Ker se boste zaradi tega popolnoma prestrašili in se obnašali kot psihopat.

906.sl_source: Že od konca šole me ignoriraš.
906.en_source: You've totally ignored me ever since high school ended.
906.sl_trans: Odkar se je končala srednja šola, me popolnoma ignoriraš.

907.sl_source: Ti si tista, ki hoče izživeti svoje osnovnošolske fantazije.
907.en_source: You're still living out some stupid seventh-grade fantasy!
907.sl_trans: Še vedno živiš v neumni fantaziji iz sedmega razreda!

909.sl_source: Uživaj živeti z očetom do konca življenja.
909.en_source: Have fun living with your dad for the rest of your life.
909.sl_trans: Zabavaj se s svojim očetom do konca življenja.

911.sl_source: Če je kaj narobe, bi rad, da se pogovoriva.
911.en_source: Because, honey, if something's wrong... I'd love it if we could talk about it.
911.sl_trans: Ker, dragi, če je kaj narobe... bi bila vesela, če bi se lahko o tem pogovorila.

915.sl_source: V redu, ker imam pomembne novice zate in če se ne počutiš dobro, se bova raje kdaj drugič pogovorila.
915.en_source: OK, because I have some very, very important news... to talk about... and if you're not feeling well, we can do this some other time.
915.sl_trans: Dobro, ker imam nekaj zelo, zelo pomembnih novic... o katerih se moram pogovoriti... in če se ne počutite dobro, lahko to storimo kdaj drugič.

916.sl_source: Zadnje čase se z Maxine veliko videvava.
916.en_source: Well, Maxine and I have been seeing a lot of each other.

917.sl_source: Razmišljala sva, da bi bilo za vse nas najbolje, da bi se jeseni preselila k nam.
917.en_source: And we were thinking it might be really best... for all of us if at the end of the summer... she came here to live with us.
917.sl_trans: Razmišljali smo, da bi bilo za vse nas najbolje, če bi konec poletja prišla živet k nam.

918.sl_source: Tako bi imela priložnost videti, kako nama gre skupaj.
918.en_source: We could really just see how we got along together.
918.sl_trans: Resnično smo lahko videli, kako se razumemo.

919.sl_source: Je to vaša prva smrtna maska?
919.en_source: Is this your first death mask?
919.sl_trans: Ali je to vaša prva maska smrti?

922.sl_source: Izpolnila sem prijavo za umetnostno akademijo.
922.en_source: I brought the application for the art academy.
922.sl_trans: Prinesel sem vlogo za umetniško akademijo.

923.en_source: I just hope it's not too late.

924.en_source: I am so sorry about what happened, Enid.
924.sl_trans: Zelo mi je žal, kar se je zgodilo, Enid.

926.sl_source: Od mene zahtevajo, da ti dam nezadostno oceno.
926.en_source: They're forcing me to give you... a non-passing grade in the class.
926.sl_trans: Prisilili so me, da ti dam oceno, ki ni bila pozitivna pri pouku.

927.sl_source: Ne morem kljub temu na akademijo?
927.en_source: Can't I still get a scholarship to the art academy?
927.sl_trans: Ali še vedno ne morem dobiti štipendije za umetniško akademijo?

929.en_source: Can you help me out here?
929.sl_trans: Ali mi lahko pri tem pomagate?

930.sl_source: Ne morem dihati pod to masko.
930.en_source: I can't breath under this mask.
930.sl_trans: Pod to masko ne morem dihati.

933.en_source: Hey, what are you doing here?

936.en_source: Can you at least let me in?
936.sl_trans: Ali me lahko vsaj spustite noter?

938.sl_source: Potrebujem nekoga, ki mi lahko nameni vsaj pet minut prijaznosti.
938.en_source: Look, I just need someone to be nice to me for five minutes.
938.sl_trans: Poglej, potrebujem samo, da je nekdo pet minut prijazen do mene.

939.en_source: Then I swear I'll leave you alone, OK?
939.sl_trans: Potem prisegam, da te bom pustil pri miru, dobro?

941.en_source: Do you have anything to drink?

942.sl_source: Tam bi moralo biti nekaj piv.
942.en_source: There might be some root beer.
942.sl_trans: Morda bo na voljo tudi korensko pivo.

945.sl_source: Odprla ga bova za obletnico dveh mesecev najine zveze.
945.en_source: We're supposed to be saving it for our two-month anniversary.
945.sl_trans: Prihranila naj bi ga za dvomesečno obletnico.

946.en_source: I mean, you like me, right, Seymour?
946.sl_trans: Saj me imaš rad, kajne, Seymour?

949.sl_source: Dana ga je kupila, ko sva šla kupovati starine.
949.en_source: Dana got it when we went shopping for antiques.
949.sl_trans: Dana ga je dobila, ko smo šli po starine.
